# EnvironmentFile for iot-ddnsd.service.
#
# IOT_DDNS_ARGS is the literal argv tail for /usr/local/bin/iot-ddnsd. The
# daemon keeps a public DNS A record pointed at the device's current public
# IPv4 (discovered via an HTTPS IP-echo, since the device only sees private/LAN
# addresses) through a pluggable provider backend. It publishes its health under
# ddns.state / ddns.last.* for the device-ui. Ships DISABLED by default. See
# /etc/iot/ds-schemas/ddns.lua and apps/docs/tdd-ddns.md.
#
# All config is hot via ds-cli (the daemon reads it at startup and re-applies on
# change). Example (DuckDNS):
#   ds-cli set ddns.provider '"duckdns"'
#   ds-cli set ddns.hostname '"mydev.duckdns.org"'
#   ds-cli set ddns.duckdns.domains '"mydev"'
#   ds-cli set ddns.duckdns.token '"<uuid>"'      # write-only secret
#   ds-cli set ddns.enabled true
#
# Providers: dyndns2 (generic: No-IP/Dynu/deSEC/IPv64/…), duckdns, cloudflare,
# route53. Secrets are write-only ds keys or a 0640 credential file referenced
# by ddns.token.path — never commit them here.

IOT_DDNS_ARGS="--ds-sock=/run/iot/data_store.sock"
